Lemon Polenta Cake
  --The Guardian
  
90 g almond meal
90 g polenta
1 tsp baking powder
pinch salt
3 eggs
1/2 c olive oil
zest and juice of 2 lemons


Preheat oven to 180C. Combine almond meal, polenta, baking powder, and salt in a bolw. In a separate bowl, combine eggs and oil until creamy; add zest and juice and combine. Fold wet into dry. Pour into small loaf or 20cm cake tin and bake until the top is golden and springy to the touch, ~30 min.
